    <note>Shen(2) Yuqiu [1460] His wife's mother was from a famous Huzhou, Wucheng Zhu(1) lineage (mingzu). Her grandfather, Lin [3259], was a student of Hu(1) Yuan [3404]. Her uncle, Fu [3256], a jinshi in 1073 was prosecuted for his friendship with Su(1) Shi [3767] and exiled to Xingguo jun where he died. Her father, Yong [3267], was famous for his scholarship in the community (xiang), but set up a hut by his father's tomb and lived in retirement (yinju). XNYL, 23.12b, 47.12a, 91.5a; Liu Yizhi, WJ, 30.3a-16b, 50.1a-3a (wife's mother, born Zhu, who died in 1145 at age 72); SS, 372.8a. CBD, 1, 697-8.</note>
